      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COMO EL VIENTO NZ (9) has been most impressive of late and made it two in a row when cruising home by 26m at his latest appearance at Williams, adding to a string of wins and placings. May need a bit of luck negotiating a very wide starting position but the form is hard to knock. VINITA ROSE NZ (8) suffered a gear malfunction and broke last week so forgive that result. Boxed on well to finish runner-up here prior. Has to contend with a very wide draw but her record at this venue is encouraging. TUMBLIN DICE (10) raced three wide without cover last start so it may pay to ignore that result and assess his chances off an easy win at Pinjarra three back. MIKIPELO (12) might need a few good breaks from an awkward draw but is building in fitness and did a good job to place here last week.",
